    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-12-15T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-12-15T18:00:00-05:00" n="307"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d307">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/808</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FDR1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Francis</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-12-15T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 15, 1917, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1906. Your 2083, December 10, just received.<note n="2" xml:id="d307fn2">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_295">p. 295</ref>.</note>
                    British Government has given Ambassador, Petrograd, liberty to withdraw Embassy
                    and leave protection of British subjects in hands of Consuls if at any time he
                    concludes that crisis should be anticipated by taking such a course, but
                    suggestion made that it may be well for him to consult his Allied colleagues
                    before taking such a step.</p>
                <p>Department approves your present course and relies on your judgment to determine
                    best future action in regard to remaining Petrograd.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
